==Events== *[[1336]] &ndash; Francesco Petrarca ([[Petrarch]]) ascends [[Mont Ventoux]]. *[[1478]] &ndash; The [[Pazzi family]] attack [[Lorenzo de' Medici]] and kill his brother [[Giuliano de' Medici|Giuliano]] during [[Solemn Mass|High Mass]] in [[Florence Cathedral]]. *[[1564]] &ndash; Playwright [[William Shakespeare]] is baptized in [[Stratford-upon-Avon]], [[Warwickshire]], England (date of actual birth is unknown). *[[1607]] &ndash; English colonists make landfall at [[Cape Henry]], [[Virginia]]. *[[1721]] &ndash; [[1721 Tabriz earthquake|A massive earthquake]] devastates the Iranian city of [[Tabriz]]. *[[1777]] &ndash; [[Sybil Ludington]], aged 16, rode {{convert|40|mi|km|abbr=out|sigfig=|sp=us}} to alert American colonial forces to the approach of the [[British Armed Forces|British regular forces]] *[[1794]] &ndash; [[Battle of Beaumont (1794)|Battle of Beaumont]] during the [[Flanders Campaign]] of the [[War of the First Coalition]]. *[[1802]] &ndash; [[Napoleon|Napoleon Bonaparte]] signs a general amnesty to allow all but about one thousand of the most notorious [[French emigration (1789–1815)|émigrés of the French Revolution]] to return to France, as part of a reconciliary gesture with the factions of the [[Ancien Régime]] and to eventually consolidate his own rule. *[[1803]] &ndash; Thousands of [[L'Aigle (meteorite)|meteor fragments fall]] from the skies of [[L'Aigle]], France; the event convinces European scientists that meteors exist. *[[1805]] &ndash; [[First Barbary War]]: [[United States Marines]] [[Battle of Derne|captured]] [[Derna, Libya|Derne]] under the command of [[First Lieutenant]] [[Presley O'Bannon]]. *[[1865]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] [[General officers in the Confederate States Army|General]] [[Joseph E. Johnston]] surrenders his army to [[General (United States)|General]] [[William Tecumseh Sherman]] at the [[Bennett Place]] near [[Durham, North Carolina]]. Also the date of [[Confederate Memorial Day]] for two states. * 1865 &ndash; [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] cavalry troopers corner and shoot dead [[John Wilkes Booth]], [[Assassination of Abraham Lincoln|assassin of President Abraham Lincoln]], in [[Virginia]]. *[[1903]] &ndash; [[Atlético Madrid]] [[Association football]] club is founded *[[1923]] &ndash; [[George VI|The Duke of York]] [[Wedding of Prince Albert, Duke of York, and Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon|weds]] [[Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother|Lady Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon]] at [[Westminster Abbey]]. *[[1925]] &ndash; [[Paul von Hindenburg]] defeats [[Wilhelm Marx]] in the second round of the [[1925 German presidential election|German presidential election]] to become the first directly elected [[head of state]] of the [[Weimar Republic]]. *[[1933]] &ndash; The [[Gestapo]], the official [[secret police|secret police force]] of [[Nazi Germany]], is established. *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Spanish Civil War]]: [[Guernica]], Spain, is [[Bombing of Guernica|bombed]] by German [[Luftwaffe]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[Benxihu Colliery]] accident in [[Manchukuo]] leaves 1549 Chinese miners dead. *[[1943]] &ndash; The [[Easter Riots]] break out in [[Uppsala]], Sweden. *[[1944]] &ndash; [[Georgios Papandreou]] becomes head of the Greek government-in-exile based in [[Egypt]]. * 1944 &ndash; [[Heinrich Kreipe]] is captured by Allied commandos in [[Axis occupation of Greece|occupied Crete]]. *[[1945]] &ndash; World War II: [[Battle of Bautzen (1945)|Battle of Bautzen]]: Last successful German tank-offensive of the war and last noteworthy victory of the [[Wehrmacht]]. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: Filipino troops of the 66th Infantry Regiment, Philippine Commonwealth Army, USAFIP-NL and the American troops of the 33rd and 37th Infantry Division, United States Army are liberated in [[Baguio City]] and they fight against the Japanese forces under General [[Tomoyuki Yamashita]]. *[[1954]] &ndash; The [[Geneva Conference (1954)|Geneva Conference]], an effort to restore peace in [[Indochina]] and Korea, begins. *[[1956]] &ndash; {{SS|Ideal X}}, the world's first successful [[container ship]], leaves [[Port Newark–Elizabeth Marine Terminal|Port Newark, New Jersey]] for [[Houston]], Texas. *[[1958]] &ndash; Final run of the [[Baltimore and Ohio Railroad]]'s ''[[Royal Blue (train)|Royal Blue]]'' from Washington, D.C., to New York City after 68&nbsp;years, the first U.S. passenger train to use [[Railway electrification system|electric locomotives]]. *[[1960]] &ndash; Forced out by the [[April Revolution]], [[President of South Korea]] [[Syngman Rhee]] resigns after 12 years of dictatorial rule. *[[1962]] &ndash; [[NASA]]'s [[Ranger 4]] spacecraft crashes into the [[Moon]]. *[[1963]] &ndash; In [[Libya]], amendments to the constitution transform Libya (United Kingdom of Libya) into one national unity ([[Kingdom of Libya]]) and allows for female participation in elections. *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Tanganyika]] and [[Zanzibar]] merge to form [[Tanzania]]. *[[1966]] &ndash; The magnitude 5.1 [[1966 Tashkent earthquake|Tashkent earthquake]] affects the largest city in [[Soviet Central Asia]] with a maximum [[Medvedev–Sponheuer–Karnik scale|MSK intensity]] of VII (''Very strong''). [[Tashkent]] is mostly destroyed and 15–200 are killed. * 1966 &ndash; A new government is formed in the [[Republic of the Congo]], led by [[Ambroise Noumazalaye]]. *[[1970]] &ndash; The [[Convention Establishing the World Intellectual Property Organization]] enters into force. *[[1981]] &ndash; Dr. [[Michael R. Harrison]] of the [[University of California, San Francisco]] Medical Center performs the world's first human open [[fetal surgery]]. *[[1982]] &ndash; Fifty-seven people are killed by former police officer [[Woo Bum-kon]] in a shooting spree in [[South Gyeongsang Province]], South Korea. *[[1986]] &ndash; A nuclear reactor accident occurs at the [[Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant]] in the [[Soviet Union]] (now [[Ukraine]]), creating the world's worst [[Chernobyl disaster|nuclear disaster]]. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[Daulatpur–Saturia tornado|The deadliest known tornado]] strikes Central Bangladesh, killing upwards of 1,300, injuring 12,000, and leaving as many as 80,000 homeless. * 1989 &ndash; ''[[People's Daily]]'' publishes the [[April 26 Editorial]] which inflames the nascent [[Tiananmen Square protests of 1989|Tiananmen Square protests]]. *[[1991]] &ndash; [[April 26, 1991 tornado outbreak|Seventy tornadoes]] break out in the central United States. Before the outbreak's end, [[Andover, Kansas]], would record the year's only [[Fujita scale|F5]] tornado. *[[1994]] &ndash; [[China Airlines Flight 140]] crashes at [[Nagoya Airfield|Nagoya Airport]] in Japan, killing 264 of the 271 people on board. *[[2002]] &ndash; Robert Steinhäuser [[Erfurt massacre|kills 16]] at [[Gutenberg-Gymnasium Erfurt|Gutenberg-Gymnasium]] in [[Erfurt]], Germany before dying of a self-inflicted gunshot. *[[2005]] &ndash; Under international pressure, [[Syria]] withdraws the last of its 14,000 troop military garrison in [[Lebanon]], ending its 29-year military domination of that country ([[Syrian occupation of Lebanon]]). *[[2018]] &ndash; American comedian [[Bill Cosby]] is [[Bill Cosby sexual assault case|found guilty of sexual assault]].
